<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28, 1903</hi></date>.
                                (Received 9.28 p.m., 29.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>May 28, 10 a.m. Am informed that the President has received a telegram
                            relating to large number United States employees lately arrived at
                            Isthmus. If explanation should be asked, what answer shall I make? If it
                            is true, it will intensify opposition to the ratification of the
                            convention.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>